# A markdown document listing Claude's VSCode extention recommendations

## Installed Extension Summary List

1. Markdown All in One
2. Markdown Preview Enhanced
3. markdownlint
4. GitLens
5. Prettier
6. Path Intellisense
7. TODO Highlight

## For Markdown

Markdown All in One - Table of contents, formatting shortcuts, preview
Markdown Preview Enhanced - Better preview with mermaid diagrams, etc.
markdownlint - Catches formatting issues (optional, can be annoying)

## For Git

GitLens - Supercharges Git integration (blame, history, comparisons)
Built-in Git is already excellent, but GitLens adds power features

## For General Development

Prettier - Code formatting (but can disable for markdown if desired)
Path Intellisense - Autocompletes file paths
TODO Highlight - Flags TODO/FIXME comments

## For Your Specific Needs

YAML - If you work with config files
HTML CSS Support - For when you peek at HTML files
